Given the following program, identify all loop structures. Please write the identified lines (just copy the first line of code from this loop, e.g., for (xxx) {, while (xxx) {.) into a list: [a list of identified lines]. If no loop is identified, just give an empty list [].. The program is struct h {
  int i;
  long j;
  int k;
};
static struct h fn1(struct h p) {
  while (1)
    p.k;
}
unsigned fn2() {
  struct h p;
  fn1(p);
  while (1) {
    struct h r;
    p = r = p;
  }
}
int main() {}
.
